    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-2367322">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-2367322">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2367322)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2367322">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tgjer" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1649421); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1649421&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252592" alt="tgjer" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1649421)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/tgjer" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1649421); return false;" >tgjer</a></span> <span class="odate time_1441023336 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">31 Aug 2015 12:15</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2367322">
									

<p>I like the humanized D-class. Though making it explicit that at least some D-class are just regular criminals, including basically just messed up kids who made some stupid decisions, makes the Foundation a lot darker.</p>
<p>My headcanon for a while has been that the &quot;D-class are all baby raping ax murderers taken from death row&quot; schtick is disinformation intended to ease researchers' consciences. If they think D-class are monsters who were already doomed before the Foundation took them, they won't feel guilty about feeding them to monsters.</p>
<p>A researcher who knows that a D-class is just a regular criminal, possibly even a criminal who hasn't killed anyone, and they're still willing to treat them as disposable sub-human specimens for horrifying experiments - that's straight up Mengele level fucked up.</p>

							</div>

								
					
