					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=348648&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610252592" alt="sirpudding" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=348648)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/sirpudding" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(348648); return false;" >sirpudding</a></span> <span class="odate time_1441050591 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">31 Aug 2015 19:49</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2367578">
									

<p>The Foundation is an international organization. There are several countries who execute far more people than the US does, and for capital &quot;crimes&quot; that we don't consider to be capital offenses in the West (or even criminal at all). Besides drug possession as I mentioned above (even in supposedly developed Singapore) Saudi Arabia for instance executes people for &quot;witchcraft and sorcerery&quot; which basically means &quot;practicing folk beliefs or owning new age or occult literature&quot;. Most of us probably have stuff on our shelves that would get us beheaded in Saudi Arabia. I certainly do.</p>

